ong>.</p></li> <li><p data-renderer-start-pos="2108"><strong data-renderer-mark="true">Proof of residential address</strong>: Required for <strong data-renderer-mark="true">directors</strong> and significant <strong data-renderer-mark="true">shareholders</strong>. (Ultimate beneficial owners or UOB)</p></li> <li><p data-renderer-start-pos="2229"><strong data-renderer-mark="true">Board Resolution</strong>: Authorize the account opening and assign signatories.</p></li> <li><p data-renderer-start-pos="2309"><strong data-renderer-mark="true">Business Plan, brochure, website:</strong>Â especially for <strong data-renderer-mark="true">newly formed companies</strong>.</p></li> <li>Contracts and sales invoices, financial statements: For the bank officer see the financial health of the company</li> <li><p data-renderer-start-pos="2408">Bank account application (provided by the bank): Â We will assist you in completing this application g to enhance your chances of success;</p></li> </ol><p data-renderer-start-pos="2574"><span style="font-size: 1rem;">Additional documents like aÂ </span><strong style="font-size: 1rem;">certificate of incumbency</strong><span style="font-size: 1rem;">Â orÂ </span><strong style="font-size: 1rem;">notarized documents</strong><span style="font-size: 1rem;"> from the home country may be required for foreign businesses</span>.</p><h2 data-renderer-start-pos="2715" id="Top-banks-in-Singapore-for-business-bank-accounts" class="indexed"><span id="top-banks-in-singapore-for-business-bank-accounts" class="anchor"></span><span class="heading_number">2.</span> <span class="heading_text">Top banks in Singapore for business bank accounts</span></h2><p data-renderer-start-pos="2766">As one of the worldâ€™s leading <strong data-renderer-mark="true">financial hubs</strong>, Singapore is home to over 150 banks regulated by the <strong data-renderer-mark="true">Monetary Authority of Singapore (MAS)</strong>.</p><p data-renderer-start-pos="2905">The top recommende